node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we spoke to @bimmawilliams, co-founder and host of the @claimastories podcast. Claima — ”claima” as in “claim a seat at the table” — is a podcast with a mission: to give young BIPOC creatives the inspiration, and roadmap, they need to make good on their ambitions. Bimma joins us from the road — specifically from, a custom-rigged 1993 Mitsubishi Delica Starwagon rechristened as “Storytella,” his mobile podcast studio during a 30-day, four-city tour of the West Coast. Here, he gives his best advice for young BIPOC creatives looking for professional advancement and shares a few of the stories that have moved him most. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.title: DMTV Milkshake: Making Space for BIPOC Creatives

node.text:
🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

LAY LO's first partnership in the ongoing series is with LA-based textile designer Warren Aldrich, who is well-known for his keen eye for pattern, color and hand-loomed fabrics. Aldrich, whose operates the eponymous clothing brand @_w.a.l.d__, hand stitched up-cycled fabrics into patchwork designs to make 21 one-of-a-kind dog bed covers. \\\ Read more about the ReMade Collection at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: This week over on @designmilktravels: The Nobu Collection’s portfolio of luxurious expressions of Japanese-inspired modern minimalism has stretched wide and far – from London to Malibu and everywhere in between – and now Nobu has claimed an address on a historic street of Poland’s capital, Warsaw. Nobu Hotels are renowned for their graceful contemporary ryokan-inspired civility superimposed across a wide variety of urban landscapes. The @nobuhotelwarsaw is arguably the collection’s most dramatic expression of this design philosophy with an artful minimalism framing the historic art-deco style throughout the hotel’s 117 rooms. \\\ Read more about the Nobu Hotel Warsaw and book your next stay in this week's #DestinationDesign. node.text: @clarepaint Founder and CEO Nicole Gibbons (@nicolegibbonsstyle) is an interior designer and entrepreneur best known for her fresh use of color and fashion-forward decorating. Nicole’s work in the design world enabled her to identify an opportunity to improve the paint-buying process from start to finish and create a better experience for young, creative home decorators. Nicole founded Clare to help people create spaces they love – and actually enjoy the process along the way. \\\ Today, Nicole joins us for Friday Five to share her favorite bombproof house plant, the best neutral paint color, a black woman-owned winery and more. node.text: It's no secret that @ikea is out to design your entire home. Beyond the standard kitchen cabinets and BILLY bookcase, IKEA has ventured into the smart home category and has produced several iterations of wireless audio speakers. Another category they’ve boldly entered is in the air purifier category, originally launching the handsomely designed and affordable FÖRNUFTIG air purifier. node.text: UNIT is a new kitchen design created by Copenhagen-based studio @aspektoffice for @reformcph. Growing out of the context of a work-from-home era, the young designers of Aspekt Office created a timeless kitchen design with a subtle home office feel. Textured paint provides depth and dimension against merging materials that include a die-cast aluminum handle rested on wooden fronts. With its appealing sense of lightness and resilient materials, UNIT is a renewal of Danish tradition, catering the changing needs of the contemporary home. \\\ Read more about UNIT at the link in bio. 🔗
